Question 1 : Create a webpage containing an image and three buttons
A. On click of the second button a change the existing image to a new image
B. On click of the third button change it once again
C. On click of first, the first image should come back

Answer 1 :

HTML Code:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <button onclick="changeimage3()">Button1</button>
    <button onclick="changeimage()">Button2</button>
    <button onclick="changeimage2()">Button3</button>
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="200px"
id="image"/>
</body>
</html>


JavaScript Code:

    const ele=document.getElementById("image");
    const newURL="data:image/jpeg;base64,"
ele.src=newURL;
}

JavaScript Code:

}
